account - Account to load by

fetchDeltaSince

public static Chargeback[] fetchDeltaSince(java.lang.String srd,
                                           java.util.Calendar timestamp,
                                           java.util.Calendar endTimestamp,
                                           int page,
                                           int pageSize)
                                    throws VindiciaReturnException,
                                           VindiciaServiceException
Returns an array of chargebacks that have been created or had status changed since the requested time. Paging is supported via page and pageSize. You should continue calling the function until the length of the resulting array is 0.

Note that if you desire all data, it is recommended that you call with a timestamp of Jan 1, 2000 00:00:00.

Parameters:
srd - sparse return descriptor
timestamp - All chargebacks on or after this timestamp
endTimestamp - All chargebacks before this timestamp
page - The offset, based on pageSize, to return.
pageSize - The number of chargebacks to return per page.
Returns:
array of Chargeback objects -
Throws:
VindiciaReturnException - for non-200 return codes from Vindicia
VindiciaServiceException
